profile_positions.description:
My main role was to deliver various digital projects on time and in budget, by planning and organising resources and  reporting progress to senior management within Pharma and Food portfolios. Led the AEO Excellence Awards winning project -  Best Use of Technology.
In addition to the below  responsibilities, I also managed a direct report (project coordinator) to ensure the highest results are delivered.

Responsibilities:

- Measure and drive onsite usage / adoption of digital products at events;

- Make sure event revenues associated with digital activities come in;

- Work with product manager and digital director to explore and develop ways to further integrate  digital activities and directories  into overall event experience;

- Work with local teams to onboard exhibitors to increase engagement level on the Food and Pharma directories;

- Project planning and scheduling, including production and implementation of a timetable and action plan;

- Liaison with contractors, suppliers and exhibitors;

- Day to day liaison with internal Event teams;

- Collecting and analyzing user profiles, usage data & market insights to inform decision-making and help test and validate assumptions.

My role was to assist the team members with day to day marketing tasks and coordinating marketing projects and activities around UBM events.

Responsibilities:
-  Improve email marketing, SEO, content marketing, social media and  user experience;

- Manage exhibition website;

- Support  the Senior Brand Manager in the consolidation strategy and development of 11 websites into one concise and brand led website;

- Produce effective marketing collaterals (delivered to d database of over 72,000);

- Identify potential online and print advertising partners.

My main role was to manage marketing activities for the world's largest humanitarian organisation based in Malta.

Responsibilities:
- Manage social media and other community activities;

- Organise courses for the Red Cross community;

 - Revamping promotion material;

 - Attend and promote the Red Cross at various events in Malta.

My main role was to put together advertising campaigns in order to generate interest in products or services. Additional to that I was responsible of the development of three publications (Latvian, Russian and English) issued by Balti Advertising Agency.

Responsibilities:

- Lead the sales and creative staff throughout the advertising process;

- Speak with clients to brainstorm advertising strategies and  relay that information back to the teams;

- Manage relationships with clients to give budget projections and ensure the creative output is reached.
